---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI @ GE" activePage="ai-use">

  <div class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-hero-label">Transparency &amp; Practice</p>
    <h1>How we use AI</h1>
    <p class="ai-hero-body">
      Good Enough is built from the ground up with AI. It's a meaningful part of how we operate, but we're deliberate about where it helps and where it doesn't belong. Here's our policy, in plain terms.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ai-grid">

    <!-- How GE uses AI -->
    <div class="ai-panel uses">
      <div class="ai-panel-label uses">Where AI helps</div>
      <h2>How GE uses AI</h2>
      <ul class="ai-list">
        <li><strong>Agentic workflows.</strong> We use AI agents to automate multi-step research, data processing, and administrative tasks end-to-end.</li>
        <li><strong>Rapid prototyping.</strong> AI accelerates early-stage design by generating working drafts of app interfaces, dashboards, data visualizations, and graphics for review and iteration.</li>
        <li><strong>Code execution.</strong> AI writes, runs, and debugs code for data analysis, automation scripts, and technical prototypes.</li>
        <li><strong>Research.</strong> AI accelerates literature reviews, policy scans, and landscape analyses by synthesizing large volumes of information quickly.</li>
        <li><strong>Planning.</strong> We use AI to structure project plans, outline deliverables, and map dependencies before work begins.</li>
        <li><strong>Guidance.</strong> AI helps surface relevant frameworks, precedents, and best practices.</li>
        <li><strong>Troubleshooting.</strong> AI assists in diagnosing technical problems, errors, and blockers across tools and workflows.</li>
        <li><strong>Meeting notetaking and storage.</strong> AI transcribes and summarizes meetings so key decisions and action items are captured and searchable.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- How GE does NOT use AI -->
    <div class="ai-panel not">
      <div class="ai-panel-label not">Where it doesn't belong</div>
      <h2>How GE does not use AI</h2>
      <ul class="ai-list">
        <li><strong>Decision-making.</strong> While AI has turbocharged our motor, you are still at the wheel. We do not automate decisions using AI. </li>
        <li><strong>Writing.</strong> Writing = thinking. Our published work, proposals, and thought leadership reflect our own thinking and voice — not AI-generated text.</li>
        
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- When GE uses AI -->
    <div class="ai-panel when">
      <div class="ai-panel-label when">Our commitments</div>
      <h2>When GE uses AI</h2>
      <ul class="ai-list">
        <li><strong>We are transparent and note that AI is being used.</strong> Clients and partners are told when AI is part of a deliverable or workflow.</li>
        <li><strong>We check for bias.</strong> We actively review AI outputs for implicit assumptions, missing perspectives, and the likelihood that skewed data were used in model training before acting on them.</li>
        <li><strong>We de-identify data and context.</strong> Sensitive client information is stripped or anonymized before being passed to any AI tool.</li>
        <li><strong>We double-check work and take responsibility for the quality of the outputs.</strong> We verify every result and stand behind everything we deliver.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ── */
  .ai-hero {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem 5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.10);
  }
  .ai-hero-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Didot', 'GFS Didot', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 52rem;
  }
  .ai-hero-body {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 44rem;
    color: var(--n700);
  }

  /* ── Policy grid ── */
  .ai-grid {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.10);
  }
  .ai-panel {
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 3rem 2.5rem;
  }
  .ai-panel-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .ai-panel-label.uses { color: var(--teal); }
  .ai-panel-label.not  { color: var(--accent); }
  .ai-panel-label.when { color: var(--cobalt); }
  .ai-panel h2 {
    font-family: 'Didot', 'GFS Didot', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .ai-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.4rem;
  }
  .ai-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--n700);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .ai-list li strong {
    color: var(--n900);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .ai-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
